    <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>RelyApply's goal is to create an information hub that can be used as a helpful tool for job seekers. Job hunting can be long and difficult. Filling out applications is time consuming. Quite often, after submitting an application, it feels like your throwing your application into a black hole hoping something comes out on the other side. It creates a sense of unease, you'll see people anxsiously looking at their phones and refreshing their emails in hopes of a proper response. The same thing happens even after interviewing, where some people have experienced waiting 6 months later just to get an email saying "We found a better candidate". It is rather inconsiderate that some companies don't take the time to inform applicants in a timely manner. People's time is very important, and it should be a common courtesy to keep them informed. RelyApply wants to be an information hub where job seekers can make informed decisions of not only who should they apply to, but also when. They'll be a bit more at ease because the information provided on RelyApply gives them an idea of when they'll hear back. By then, they can make informed an informed decision by either choosing an company/employer that is more prompt or they know when they should contact the company/employer for a follow-up.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>RelyApply will not surpress or change any review.</p></li>
          <li><p>When creating an account, user's are required to use an email and create a password. They can also log in with their Facebook or Gmail Account.</p></li>
          <li><p>We require users to confirm their emails to help ensure the integrity of their profile.</p></li>
          <li><p>The review forms in RelyApply have been created in order to state information in the most terse way possible. Comments have not been enabled when submitting reviews. The review forms simply ask how long did it take to hearback, where, and some details regarding the user's experience and the application/interview's details.</p></li>
          <li><p>When applicants submit reviews to a company/employer, RelyApply takes no sides. If reviews were found to be created out of coercion, they will be removed.</p></li>
          <li><p>When writing a review, you are sharing your opinions based on what you felt was a proper follow-up after applying. We ask that your review be truthful.</p></li>
          <li><p>Companies need at least 5 reviews to show a postive or negative responsiveness indicator.</p></li>
          <li><p>Normally, if it's been over a month, and you haven't heard back, the position you applied for may have been filled. However, some companies don't bother telling applicants.</p></li>
          <li><p>Companies usually get back within a couple of weeks on average.</p></li>
          <li><p>Depending on the industry, average follow-up times can vary.
          We ask users to please be honest with their reviews.
          Sections marked with "*" are required.</p></li>
          <li><p>You can only submit one Application and one Interview review per company/employer for every quarter of the year.</p></li>
          <li><p>If you see incorrect information on a company/employer's profile, registered users can go to the respective company/employer's profile and click the link to make a request to edit those details. Once they are approved by RelyApply's administrators, the changes will be made.</p></li>
        </ul>
