        <p>According to precendents set by United States law, RelyApply is not legally responsible for the content and reviews submitted by RelyApply's users. This can be found in Section 230 of Title 47 of the United States Code as part of the Communication Decency Act of 1996. "By its plain language, ยง 230 creates a federal immunity to any cause of action that would make service providers liable for information originating with a third-party user of the service".
        -<a href="https://ilt.eff.org/Zeran_v._America_Online%2c_Inc.html">Zervan v. American Online, Inc.</a></p>
        <br>
        <p>Here is a list of key cases that show this U.S. code is currently upheld: <a href="https://www.eff.org/issues/cda230">https://www.eff.org/issues/cda230</a></p>
