      <div class="card-body">
        <p>RelyApply will not take down reviews because an company/employer asked us to. If the employer who threatened or pursued legal action is found to be done under false circumstances, RelyApply will take legal action against them. When an employer threatens or pursues legal action against our users due to a negative review, RelyApply will review the issue and see if they aligned with our guidelines. Payment to remove such reviews is also not accepted. RelyApply does not favor either side. If a review violates an agreement/policy between a user and an company/employer, RelyApply will not determine whether or not the supposedely offended party is in the right. Please remember, that RelyApply is not going to validate the truthfullness of each review submitted. Any suppossed proof that the reviews are incorrect will be turned down and ignored. Letters may be posted on our website and/or posted on <a href="https://www.lumendatabase.org/">lumendatabase.org</a>, a "database collects and analyzes legal complaints and requests for removal of online materials, helping Internet users to know their rights and understand the law. These data enable us to study the prevalence of legal threats and let Internet users see the source of content removals". A notification will also be placed on the employer's company/employer profile.</p>
        <p>If you feel you have to provide legal documents to RelyApply, please send us a message on our contact page. If the employer who threatened or pursued legal action is found to be done under false circumstances, RelyApply will take legal action against them.</p>

